How Aziz Hashim Is Changing The Franchising Landscape



















We Are Re-defining Private Equity...
...in franchise and chain business investing. We believe in the total alignment of interests among our key stakeholders – the management team of our Portfolio Companies, our Fund Investors (predominantly multi-unit/multi-brand franchisees), and our Fund’s operationally-experienced Partners. Through our unique access to multi-unit franchisees and wider networks, NRD is the next evolution of the franchise private equity space.













We Are Financial And Strategic Partners
Because we are operators and we’ve walked in Founder/Owner/Entrepreneur/Executive shoes, we know money isn’t the answer to all business goals. Oftentimes, when businesses are at critical junctures in their life cycles, expertise, resources, an outside perspective and seasoned guidance are just as crucial as cash to building a dynamic and sustainable business. When a business merits not only capital, but also operational and strategic support, NRD Capital shines as the partner who provides both.















We Are Franchisee-centric
While we invest in franchisors, we are franchisee-centric. We are focused on the unit-level profitability of every brand we evaluate, especially for those we invest in. Our mission is to invest in brands that offer superior products/services and compelling unit-level economics in order to help them strategically grow through the power of franchising. We believe that when franchisees and franchisors work together as partners, all parties win.

















The NRD Difference





OUR FUND







OUR MANAGEMENT







OUR MOTIVATION











OUR FUND
NRD Capital occupies a unique niche among franchise equity investors. Our fund invests with small to medium-sized franchisors, infuses capital and applies our operating expertise to grow those brands. We look at franchise companies not just as financial investments, but as living entities in which concept founders/management and franchisees have invested substantial amounts of time and resources. Our goal is to use our operational and financial experience to position high quality brands for accelerated but responsible growth.


OUR MANAGEMENT
Our team has extensive franchise experience spanning single store operations to public companies. At our core, we are operators. Collectively, our team has been involved with 20 brands including top global companies like Popeyes, Burger King, Subway and Domino's. We’ve also worked with major regional brands such as Moe's Southwest Grill, Pet Valu, Super Wash and local startups like Urban Grounds and Tutor Force. Our experience encompasses every area of the franchise business model from sales, financing and real estate development to operations, marketing, HR  technology and successful exit strategies.


OUR MOTIVATION
Our fund was born when our Founder, Aziz Hashim, set out to fulfill two goals: 1) to put 1,000 entrepreneurs into business and 2) to provide our franchisee-investors with an opportunity to participate in business as franchisors. The core pillar of NRD's strategy is to invest in brands where franchisee success is the central value.

 
 
 




