Susan E. Beth
Chief Operating Officer
Susan E. Beth, CFE, is the COO at NRD Capital.  Susan was previously a Vice President and the Chief Operating Officer of Super Wash, Inc., the nation’s largest franchisor of self-serve car washes.  Susan is a member of the Board of Directors of the International Franchise Association (IFA), and is a motivational speaker on topics such as: passionate leadership; embracing change; building committed teams, rewarding relationships and dynamic cultures; visionary entrepreneurship; and goal-setting.  
Susan received the IFA’s prestigious Bonny LeVine Award for mentoring and promoting women in franchising in 2012; she is also the proud recipient of the 2013 Crystal Compass given by the IFA’s Women’s Franchise Committee celebrating leadership in franchising, company and/or community; and she was featured in the January 2011 issue of Franchise Times as one of the “20 to Watch” in 2011. 

                        Susan grew up in a family business and has been immersed in business operations for 30+ years.  She took her first leap into business ownership when she bought her first franchise at the age of 19.  She went on to acquire two more locations and was a multi-unit franchisee with her business partner for 9 years.  Always one to try and “fill a need” when a unique business opportunity presents itself, Susan founded three franchise-related businesses by the time she turned 35.  
                        

                        One such unique business opportunity is the ground-breaking “Franchise Capital Exchange, (FCX)” of which she is the creator and founder. FCX is a one of a kind event whereby franchise companies are connected with the financial and human capital they need to grow their systems.
                        

                        Susan is the Past Chair of the International Franchise Association’s (IFA) Women’s Franchise Committee; the co-founder and past Co-Chair of the Chicago Women’s Franchise Network; and the past Co-Chair for the Strategic Advisory Board of International Institute for Franchise Education based at Nova Southeastern University.  
                        









Aziz Hashim  
Managing Partner
Aziz Hashim is one of the world’s leading experts on franchising and a highly regarded executive in the U.S. and international franchise space. He is the Founder and Managing Partner of NRD Capital (NRD), the first business fund both sponsored and managed by a former multi-unit franchisee. He also serves as Chairman of the Board of Directors for the International Franchise Association (IFA), representing the franchise industry and its $1.3 trillion in annual economic output.
Mr. Hashim’s franchise portfolio began with one QSR location and he has since grown it to become one of the top 200 franchise operators in the country, representing a number of high-profile brands, including Popeye’s®, KFC®, Taco Bell®, Dominos Pizza® and many others. NRD Capital, founded in 2014, now occupies a unique niche in franchise equity investments. Based in Atlanta, NRD Capital is focused on supporting the growth of high quality franchise brands by positioning them for accelerated success, and its portfolio now includes successful QSR concepts like Fuzzy’s Taco Shop and the iconic American brand Frisch’s Big Boy, acquired by NRD in 2015 through an investor group made up of greater than 80 percent multi-unit franchisees. NRD Capital now boasts more than 75 years of collective operational and financial experience with top global brands like Burger King and Snap Fitness as well as regional brands like Moe’s Southwest Grill, Pet Valu, Super Wash.
Mr. Hashim was named by Nation’s Restaurant News as one of the 50 most powerful people leading and shaping change in the restaurant industry, and he serves on the Board of Advisors at the J. Mack Robinson College of Business at Georgia State University, the BB&T Bank Regional Advisory Board. He also served as past Chairman of the 2014 Multi-Unit Franchise Conference.
Deeply involved in community service and frequently contributing to the industry’s growth, Mr. Hashim regularly shares his knowledge and experience at major business and franchise conferences. In 2014, Mr. Hashim and his wife endowed a faculty position at the Cecil B. Day School of Hospitality at Georgia State University for the Study of Franchise Entrepreneurship. His dynamic leadership and strategy for success is reflected both in his compelling message to the industry and in NRD’s significant and consistent innovation and growth. Mr. Hashim attended the University of California at Irvine, graduating with honors from its prestigious electrical engineering program.









Shawn Lederman
Director
Shawn Lederman is a Director with NRD Capital.  Mr. Lederman has over 17 years of private equity, finance, and consulting experience in strategic planning, corporate revitalization, turnarounds, and M&A.
Prior to joining NRD, Mr. Lederman worked as a Director on the Private Equity Team at Highland Capital Management, L.P.  In this capacity, Mr. Lederman was involved with all aspects of the firm’s investment process, including sourcing new opportunities, leading due diligence, negotiation and financing, supporting operations, planning and integration of successful acquisitions, portfolio monitoring, and Board governance.  Previously, Mr. Lederman was a Vice President at Buccino & Associates, Inc., a middle market consulting firm that specialized in working with troubled companies.  In his role, Mr. Lederman was involved with the assessment, reorganization and recapitalization of companies in the manufacturing, healthcare, food, and retail industries.  Prior to joining Buccino, Mr. Lederman was a Consultant at Putnam, Hayes, & Bartlett and later Charles River Associates, Inc.  In these roles, Mr. Lederman worked on behalf of major electric utility companies, evaluating their strategic alternatives in a deregulating environment, analyzing merger and acquisition candidates, and assessing the market value of electric generating and transmission assets.
Mr. Lederman earned his M.B.A. from New York University’s Stern School of Business with distinction and received his B.S. in Finance and International Management from Boston University where he graduated summa cum laude.









Richard Pawlowski
Director
NRD Capital Management (“NRD Capital) is very pleased to announce the addition of Richard Pawlowski to the team.  Richard Pawlowski is a Director with NRD Capital.  Before joining NRD, Richard was Chief Financial Officer of Famous Dave’s of America Inc. (NASDAQ:DAVE). Famous Dave’s is the largest domestic chain of full-service BBQ restaurants with approximately $450mm in system-wide sales from a mix of over 170 company, and franchised locations.
Prior to Famous Dave’s he was a manager at Bain & Company where he led and managed consulting projects in the retail and private equity industries, including helping to develop a new strategy and brand position for a $1.3B revenue polished casual restaurant chain. Earlier in his career he co-founded a successful multi-unit, multi-brand franchised-restaurant development acquisition and operating company, that he grew to generate over $30mm in annual revenue.
Richard received his Master of Business Administration from Harvard Business School and his Master of Engineering from the University of Oxford.









Harrison Price
Principal
Harrison Price has over 20 years of M&A advisory, corporate finance, and financial restructuring experience. His background spans numerous buy-side, sell-side, and capital raising engagements, for both financially healthy and underperforming businesses.
Mr. Price has completed over 60 financial advisory engagements across all major industry sectors. He has arranged private capital transactions totaling several billion dollars with institutional debt and equity sources.  Mr. Price has also assisted underperforming companies in raising capital and completing financial restructurings.  He has testified in federal court as an expert on a variety of M&A matters including the effectiveness of marketing processes used in selling companies, the adequacy of due diligence efforts, and the valuation of businesses.  
During his career Mr. Price has worked on a wide variety of transactions including private offerings of debt and equity, debt restructurings, and sales and acquisitions of companies.  Representative transactions include acquiring several franchisee groups of a major fast food brand and then selling the business for $30m; arranging $866m of senior and junior debt for a specialty retailer; advising a $40m manufacturer of casual travel gear in replacing its credit facility; selling a $15m engine remanufacturer to a financial buyer; and advising a $370m manufacturer of food-grade specialty chemicals during its downsizing and financial restructuring.
Prior to joining our firm Mr. Price was a Managing Director in the investment banking group at Telos Capital Advisors, LLC.  Mr. Price earned his B.S. in Economics and his J.D., each from the University of North Carolina.









Brianna Williams
Dir. of Investor Relations
Brianna Williams joined NRD in 2013 where she serves as Executive Assistant to Aziz Hashim, and the Director of Investor Relations. She coordinates with investors, oversees the day-to-day, and assists with long term, operations of the office. In addition, she also provides administrative support to other executives and directors when needed. Brianna is the liaison between the Executive Committee and outside
    vendors. 
Prior to joining NRD, Brianna worked for a Germany-based investment firm as an Office Manager. She has provided administrative support for over 7 years.
In 2012, Brianna graduated with a BA in International Affairs and Political Science from The George Washington University in Washington, D.C.












